modules.description: Provides functions to parse, format, and manipulate time values using nanosecond precision. Operates on custom time representations and duration calculations. Enables accurate logging of event timestamps and computation of time intervals in real-time applications.

Manages scheduled events and signals with precise timing control, allowing for delayed execution and timestamped triggers. It operates on float-based time and duration values, supporting one-time and recurring event scheduling. Use cases include coordinating timed animations, managing delayed user interactions, and synchronizing asynchronous processes.
